<br>
What i know:<br>
<br>
When you walk into your apartment you do get a key assigned to you automatically.  Remember what city and apartment complex you are in.<br>
<br>
You can furnish your apartment.  I have a floor hurricane lamp, a table blue lamp, a stereo and a painting in mine.  There are shops they sell items for your apartment.  I have even seen a refrigerator in one shop.  When you get a furnishing or item to put in your apartment all you do is pick up the item out of your inventory and have it on your cursor.  Then just put the cursor where you want the item and drop it (think its right click hehe).  Your item will be placed where you put it.  Your items can be picked up and moved as many times as you want.  The items stay in your apartment.  I must say it is pretty cool because the lamps actually add lighting effects to it and everything.<br>
<br>
Rumors but i have not confirmed:<br>
<br>
Its said you can invite friends into your apartment to hand out and have meetings.  Its said this feature is not yet in the game till it goes live.<br>
<br>
Its said you will be able to expand your apartment.  I guess this feature is not part of beta if its a feature at all.<br>
<br>
Its said you can destroy your key and then walk into a new apartment complex to get a new apartment.  Im sure you will lose all items in your apartment if you do this and if you can actually destroy your key.<br>
<br>
That is what i know on apartments if i find out anything new ill let you all know.<br>
<br>
